\c 2
\p
\v 1 I will stand upon my watch, and set me upon the tower, and will watch to
see what he will say unto me, and what I shall answer when I am reproved. 
\v 2 And the LORD answered me, and said, Write the vision, and make 
\add it\add* plain upon tables, that he may run that readeth it. 
\v 3 For the vision \add is\add* yet for an appointed time, but at the end it
shall speak, and not lie: though it tarry, wait for it; because it will surely
come, it will not tarry. 
\v 4 Behold, his soul \add which\add* is lifted up is not upright in him: but
the just shall live by his faith.
\p
\v 5 Yea also, because he transgresseth by wine, \add he is\add* a proud man,
neither keepeth at home, who enlargeth his desire as hell, and \add is
\add* as death, and cannot be satisfied, but gathereth unto him all nations,
and heapeth unto him all people: 
\v 6 Shall not all these take up a parable against him, and a taunting proverb
against him, and say, Woe to him that increaseth \add that which is
\add* not his! how long? and to him that ladeth himself with thick clay! 
\v 7 Shall they not rise up suddenly that shall bite thee, and awake that
shall vex thee, and thou shalt be for booties unto them? 
\v 8 Because thou hast spoiled many nations, all the remnant of the people
shall spoil thee; because of men’s blood, and \add for\add* the violence of
the land, of the city, and of all that dwell therein.
\p
\v 9 Woe to him that coveteth an evil covetousness to his house, that he may
set his nest on high, that he may be delivered from the power of evil! 
\v 10 Thou hast consulted shame to thy house by cutting off many people, and
