\v 3 God came from Teman, and the Holy One from mount Paran. Selah. His glory
covered the heavens, and the earth was full of his praise. 
\v 4 And \add his\add* brightness was as the light; he had horns \add coming
\add* out of his hand: and there \add was\add* the hiding of his power. 
\v 5 Before him went the pestilence, and burning coals went forth at his
feet. 
\v 6 He stood, and measured the earth: he beheld, and drove asunder the
